{"actor":"Ethan Miller","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T22:22:38Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":41,"issue_id":"mindsculptor-npo","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"mindsculptor-npo\",\"title\":\"Remove Render background worker service\",\"description\":\"mindsculptor-scraper worker service in render.yaml restarts immediately after each run (Render default behavior). The cron job already handles 12h scheduling. Worker is redundant and would hammer MTGO continuously. Remove the worker service block from render.yaml.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"ethan.w.miller@outlook.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:18Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ethan Miller\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:18Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Ethan Miller","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T22:22:39Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":42,"issue_id":"mindsculptor-dph","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"mindsculptor-dph\",\"title\":\"Fix inferTier to return null for unknown events\",\"description\":\"inferTier() in src/parsers/mtgo.ts defaults to 'challenge' when no pattern matches. This silently misclassifies unknown events (Opens, Pro Tours, etc). Return null instead — the column is nullable and the check constraint allows it.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"ethan.w.miller@outlook.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ethan Miller\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Ethan Miller","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T22:22:39Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":43,"issue_id":"mindsculptor-0g1","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"mindsculptor-0g1\",\"title\":\"DRY MTGO types: export from scraper, import in parser\",\"description\":\"MtgoCard, MtgoDeck, MtgoStanding, MtgoEventData, FORMAT_MAP, and extractEventData are duplicated between src/scrapers/mtgo.ts and src/parsers/mtgo.ts. Export them from the scraper and import in the parser to eliminate the copy-paste divergence risk.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"ethan.w.miller@outlook.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ethan Miller\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Ethan Miller","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T22:22:39Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":44,"issue_id":"mindsculptor-vqc","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"mindsculptor-vqc\",\"title\":\"Add fetch timeout to MTGO scraper\",\"description\":\"fetchHtml() in src/scrapers/mtgo.ts has no timeout. If mtgo.com hangs, the cron/worker hangs until Render kills the process. Add AbortController with 30s timeout.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"ethan.w.miller@outlook.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ethan Miller\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\"}"}
{"actor":"Ethan Miller","comment":null,"created_at":"2026-03-01T22:22:39Z","event_type":"status_changed","id":45,"issue_id":"mindsculptor-8mx","new_value":"{\"status\":\"in_progress\"}","old_value":"{\"id\":\"mindsculptor-8mx\",\"title\":\"Fix O(n^2) indexOf in scrape loop\",\"description\":\"newUrls.indexOf(url) called inside for...of loop in scrapeNewMtgoEvents() is O(n^2). Trivial fix: use for...of with entries() or a counter index.\",\"status\":\"open\",\"priority\":2,\"issue_type\":\"task\",\"owner\":\"ethan.w.miller@outlook.com\",\"created_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\",\"created_by\":\"Ethan Miller\",\"updated_at\":\"2026-03-02T06:22:28Z\"}"}
